org.typemeta.funcj.control

Interface Try<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the successful result type
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Try.Failure, Try.Success

    public interface Try<T>
    Union type of a successful result and an exception.

    A Try<T> value is either the sub-type Try.Failure<T> which wraps an exception, or the sub-type Try.Success<T> which wraps a value of type T.

    Try is biased towards the Try.Success<T>, meaning that map, apply and flatMap operate on the Success value and bypass the Failure value.

    Null values are not allowed.
